org.jdesktop.jdic.browser
Class WebBrowser

java.lang.Object
  java.awt.Component
      java.awt.Canvas
          org.jdesktop.jdic.browser.WebBrowser
All Implemented Interfaces:
javax.accessibility.Accessible, java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable
public class WebBrowser
extends java.awt.Canvas

A WebBrowser component represents a blank rectangular area of the screen onto which the application can display webpages or from which the application can trap events from the browser window. In order to show WebBrowser component in GUI, user need to add WebBrowser to a top-level container, such as Frame.

The class that is interested in processing an WebBrowser event should implement interface WebBrowserListener, and the object created with that class should use WebBrowser's addWebBrowserListener method to register as a listener.

The WebBrowser has a inner class Status. User can use getStatus method to retrieve the Status object of this WebBrowser. Querying status of this WebBrowser can be done by calling methods provided by class Status.

Version:
0.1, 03/07/17
Author:
Kyle Yuan
